<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include('includes/head', { title: 'How to file a claim', nonce: nonce }) %>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.folder/possibleDisabilities.css" />

  <body>
    <div class="page-wrapper">
      <%- include('includes/header', { nonce: nonce }) %>

      <div class="container">
      <h1>How to file a claim</>
      <h2>Step 0</h2>
         <p>VA disability is following 3 major requirements </p>
           <p>Connection to your service. The onset of your condition needs to be linked to the time of active service</p>
           <p>The condition needs to be chronic</p>
           <p>It has to affect your ability to perform your daily duties and responsibilities</p>
      <h3>Dirrect connection claim</h3>
      <h2>Step 1</h2>
         <p>Start the intent to file</p>
         <p>Once you submit an Intent to File, you protect your effective date. From that day, you’ll have 1 year to complete your claims while still being eligible for retroactive pay</p>
         <p><a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-21-0966/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> Intent to File (VA Form 21-0966)</a></p>
      <h2>Step 2</h2>
         <p>FOIA (Freedom of Information Act)</p>
           <p>Request a full military record through <a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-20-10206/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> FOIA (VA Form 20-10206)</a></p>
           <p>This may take several months to a year, so start early</p>
           <p>Full military and medical records, including service treatment records, personnel file, and C-File</p>
         <h2>Step 3</h2>
           <p>Personal Statement: Describe your disability, when/how it began, and how it affects daily life and employment.<a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-21-4138/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
  VA Form 21-4138 – Personal Statement in Support of Claim</a></p>
           <p>Lay Statements: Ask family, friends, or coworkers who have observed your condition to provide statements.<a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-21-10210/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
  Lay Statement (VA Form 21-10210)</a></p>
           <p>Buddy Statements: If possible, ask a fellow service member to confirm in-service events, injuries, or stressors that may not appear in your records <a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-21-10210/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
 Buddy Statement (VA Form 21-10210)</a></p>
           <p> Gather all the medical records of any specific condition-related visit to a medical professional outside the VA </p>
           <p>If VA medical records are available through Blue Button, FOIA, or Inservice records, highlight the events that pertain to the specific disability claim and create a separate file consisting of pages with highlighted references.</p>
           
        <div class="spacer"></div>
      </div> <!-- closes .container -->

      <%- include('includes/footer') %>
    </div> <!-- closes .page-wrapper -->

    <!-- Your existing scripts -->
    <script src="/js/mobile-drawer.js" nonce="<%= nonce %>"></script>
    <script src="/js/symptomAnalysis.js" nonce="<%= nonce %>" defer></script>
  </body>
</html>
